{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_30","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `org.apache.maven:maven-resolver-provider:3.9.12` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3814-library-new-request-org.apache.maven-maven-resolver-provider-3.9.12-2fe82576\n\nThe most likely blocking stage was Gradle `nativeTest`, not source generation itself. In `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.maven:maven-resolver-provider:3.9.12/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-28T11-26-03-686403Z.log`, 5 native tests fail and all of them collapse in `Maven_resolver_providerTest.newRepositorySystem()` with `Expecting actual not to be null` when `locator.getService(RepositorySystem.class)` is resolved. That points to missing or too-late native-image metadata around the Maven Resolver provider / `DefaultServiceLocator` path. Earlier iterations also had generated-test instability: `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.maven:maven-resolver-provider:3.9.12/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-28T11-14-50-016692Z.log` fails compilation because `RecordingWorkspaceReader` does not implement `getRepository()`, and `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.maven:maven-resolver-provider:3.9.12/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-28T11-15-03-343867Z.log` fails a JVM assertion in `mavenWorkspaceReaderSuppliesModelWithoutRemoteRepositories()`.\n\nMetrics also ended in failure after 6 iterations (`stats/org.apache.maven/maven-resolver-provider/3.9.12/execution-metrics.json`), and dynamic-access coverage is effectively unavailable (`tests/src/org.apache.maven/maven-resolver-provider/3.9.12/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` is `0/0`). There is useful follow-up work captured separately in `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.maven:maven-resolver-provider:3.9.12/metadata-fix/codex.log`; a later rerun in `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.maven:maven-resolver-provider:3.9.12/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-28T11-40-13-673915Z.log` shows all 6 native tests passing after metadata repairs, so this looks salvageable but still needs manual review and commit.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch together with `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.maven:maven-resolver-provider:3.9.12/metadata-fix/codex.log`, focusing on the generated test and the provider / service-locator metadata changes.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.maven:maven-resolver-provider:3.9.12` from that preserved work and confirm `nativeTest` stays green.\n3. If it passes, commit the metadata repair and open or update the manual PR for issue `#3814`."}}
